gomodel:SYNGO_2609  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From Results section:\n\n\"syntaxin 1A and nSec-1/Munc18-a were efficiently co-immunoprecipitated with anti-Vps11 antibody but not by normal rabbit IgG negative controls. This interaction is specific to the syntaxin 1A and nSec-1/Munc18-a, because other core components in the neuron specific membrane fusion, such as SNAP-25 and VAMP2, did not interact (Fig. 1A). To further confirm this interaction, we performed GST-pull down assays using rat brain homogenates. The endogenous mammalian Class C Vps protein complex was efficiently retained by GST-syntaxin 1A and GST-nSec-1/Munc18-a (Fig. 1B, lane 2 and lane 5), but not GST, GST-SNAP-25, or GST-VAMP2, respectively.\"\n\n\"Synaptosomal fractions were prepared from adult rat cortex [18,19]. The distribution profile of mammalian Class C Vps proteins was almost identical to those of syntaxin 1A, nSec-1/Munc18-a, and synaptophysin, which are found in fractions containing synaptic cytosolic and vesicular proteins\"\n\n\"Using primary hippocampal neuronal cultures, mammalian Class C Vps proteins also co-localized with synapsin 1-positive processes and punctate synapses (Supplemental Fig. 2).\"\n\n22/2/2018 Pim\n- The data in the paper do not definitively place VPS18 in the presynapse (SV enrichment in Fig.1 might). However, In Fig.5 a role in the presynapse in SV ecocytsis is demonstrated. So, I agree to 'presynapse (GO:0098793)' based on the weak evidence.. Experimental description: From M&M section:\n\"For immunoprecipitation, rat brain homogenates were lysed in modified RIPA buffer.\"\n\"Primary hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from neonatal rat pus (Sprague-Dawley)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2609" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

